&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;YHMO03-2 Medicines Optimisation Pharmacist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The NECS Medicines Optimisation team is a well-established team of pharmacists, technicians and support staff with a proven track record in delivering medicines optimisation services. We are looking for an enthusiastic and dynamic pharmacist to join our Yorkshire and Humber team delivering CCG / practice based medicines optimisation services across the 4 Humber CCGs (East Riding of Yorkshire, Hull, North East Lincolnshire and North Lincolnshire).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be self-motivated, able to work independently and passionate about providing the highest standards of care to patients in primary care. Key areas of work will include working within your clinical competencies as part of a multi-disciplinary team to provide expertise in clinical medicines management to practice teams and GP practices.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will also be required to contribute towards practice and PCN financial and quality performance. You will work to deliver medicines optimisation initiatives within GP practices and PCNs including the provision of specialist professional pharmaceutical advice and services to ensure the safe and cost effective use of medicines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will have excellent written and verbal communication skills and inter-personal skills, experience of working in multidisciplinary teams and influencing others. Leadership, motivational, IT skills and excellent communication skills are essential to this role. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A working knowledge of SystmOne and EMISweb GP clinical systems would be an advantage. The post-holder will be required to travel on a regular basis between GP practices and NECS bases across the Humber area.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will be held virtually via Microsoft Teams w/c 30&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Any further queries please contact&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Clare Grantham - clare.grantham@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Karen Hiley - karen.hiley@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sharan Bassan - gursharan.bassan@nhs.net &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
